    • Method Detail

      • getTemplateDirection

        public static Direction getTemplateDirection(Direction facing,
                             ObstacleTemplate template)
        Selects a facing suitable for the template. If given facing isn't suitable, nearest suitable direction is selected, preferring directions in clockwise order.
        Parameters:
        facing - select template facing nearest to this obstacle facing
        template - select facing for this template
        Returns:
        facing for the template (null if facing parameter was null)

      • getTemplateDirection

        public static Direction getTemplateDirection(Direction newFacing,
                             Direction oldFacing,
                             ObstacleTemplate template)
        Determines a template's facing direction after it's turned. Result is undefined if old facing isn't a valid facing for the template.
        Parameters:
        newFacing - facing direction after turning (may be invalid for the template)
        oldFacing - facing direction before turning (must be valid for the template)
        template - the template
        Returns:
        a valid facing direction adjacent to the given new facing (null if either direction parameter was null)

      • isTemplateDirection

        public static boolean isTemplateDirection(ObstacleTemplate template,
                          Direction facing)
        Checks if a given facing is suitable for a template.
        Parameters:
        template - check if the facing is suitable for this template
        facing - check if this facing is suitable for the template
        Returns:
        the facing is suitable for the template

      • getTemplateDirections

        public static Direction[] getTemplateDirections(ObstacleTemplate template)
        Get possible template directions for a template. A template can't be placed facing a direction which doesn't identify the tiles that belong to the template.
        Parameters:
        template - get possible facing directions for this template
        Returns:
        possible directions (copy array)

      • getMoveDirections

        public static Direction[] getMoveDirections(Direction facing,
                            MovementTemplate template)
        Get directions where a template can be moved without turning in place. The returned array can be empty if facing is null or facing is invalid for the template.
        Parameters:
        facing - template's facing
        template - get possible movement directions for this template
        Returns:
        possible movement directions (copy array)
